default3.3.6:  Part Load FactordefaultCOPs are reduced by part load running.  This is a potent source of pump efficiency problems when pumps operate at below half power.  At 0 part load the efficiency becomes 0%.  All pumps that are sized to deli
defaultver the full heat load of a house at -15, or -10C when pump COPs are reduced, are going to normally operate in a low or very low part load condition at more usual temperatures.  
